qas.question: Who pledged to respect the constitutional order of succession?
Who won the election in June 2009?

context: On 2 March 2009, however, <a0_0>Vieira<a0_0/> was assassinated by what preliminary reports indicated to be a group of soldiers avenging the death of the head of joint chiefs of staff, <a1_0>General Batista Tagme Na Wai<a1_0/>. Tagme died in an explosion on Sunday, 1 March 2009, target of an assassination. <a2_0>Military leaders<a2_0/> in the country pledged to respect the constitutional order of succession. National Assembly Speaker <a3_0>Raimundo Pereira<a3_0/> was appointed as an interim president until a nationwide election on 28 June 2009. It was won by <a4_0>Malam Bacai Sanhá<a4_0/>.
